{{Short description|Kofun in Koryo, Nara, Japan}}
[[File:Suyama_kofun_stereo.jpg|thumb|270x270px|Suyama Kofun ]]
{{Coord|34|33|23|N|135|44|27|E|display=title}}'''Suyama Kofun''' ({{Lang-ja|巣山古墳}}<ref>{{Cite web|title=巣山古墳 {{!}} 奈良県歴史文化資源データベース {{!}} 奈良県歴史文化資源データベース「いかす・なら」|url=http://www.pref.nara.jp/miryoku/ikasu-nara/bunkashigen/main00243.html|access-date=2021-07-17|website=www.pref.nara.jp}}</ref>) is a [[Kofun]] that is located in [[Kōryō, Nara]] of [[Japan]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=巣山古墳 文化遺産オンライン|url=https://bunka.nii.ac.jp/heritages/detail/163321|access-date=2021-07-17|website=bunka.nii.ac.jp}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=観光　巣山古墳概要 {{!}} 広陵町|url=https://www.town.koryo.nara.jp/contents_detail.php?co=kak&frmId=28|access-date=2021-07-17|website=www.town.koryo.nara.jp}}</ref> It is designated as a national [[Special Historic Site]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=小項目事典|first=国指定史跡ガイド,精選版 日本国語大辞典,百科事典マイペディア,知恵蔵,ブリタニカ国際大百科事典|title=巣山古墳とは|url=https://kotobank.jp/word/%E5%B7%A3%E5%B1%B1%E5%8F%A4%E5%A2%B3-85101|access-date=2021-07-17|website=コトバンク|language=ja}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=国指定文化財等データベース|url=https://kunishitei.bunka.go.jp/heritage/detail/401/1959|access-date=2021-07-17|website=kunishitei.bunka.go.jp}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=巣山古墳（すやまこふん）|url=https://www.library.pref.nara.jp/nara_2010/0425.html|access-date=2021-07-17|website=www.library.pref.nara.jp}}</ref> It has a length of about 204 metres.<ref name=":0">{{Cite journal|last=Edwards|first=Walter|date=2000|title=Contested Access: The Imperial Tombs in the Postwar Period|url=https://www.jstor.org/stable/133273|journal=Journal of Japanese Studies|volume=26|issue=2|pages=375|doi=10.2307/133273|issn=0095-6848}}</ref> As of 2000, it was one of a small handful of ''kofun'' tombs over 200 metres in length which were not administered by the [[Imperial Household Agency]], as it is not thought to be directly connected to [[Imperial House of Japan|the Imperial line]].<ref name=":0" />

